(: Open a JNDI directory context :)
"jndi:get-dir-context($properties as element()?) as xs:long? — opens a JNDI directory context with properties: <properties><property name='java.naming.provider.url' value='ldap://localhost:389'/><property name='java.naming.factory.initial' value='com.sun.jndi.ldap.LdapCtxFactory'/></properties>"
